    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "But it's not just a moment of sadness... it's a conclusion. The tragedy isn't that he left, but that the story itself has reached its natural, inevitable end. To force a character to keep wandering through a ruined landscape when the play is clearly over... doesn't that feel cruel? There is a dark, poetic beauty in a graceful exit, a way to preserve the memory of what was before it turns into something ugly and desperate. Why must every story be forced to endure through the decay?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
